      "value": "<p>A whirlwind of blades, borers, gears, and scoops designed for mining form this mech base.</p>\n<p><strong>Base HP</strong> +4; <strong>Hit Point Advancement</strong> +1</p>\n<p><strong>EAC</strong> +0; <strong>KAC</strong> +2; <strong>Fort</strong> +1; <strong>Ref</strong> +0</p>\n<p><strong>Lower Limb Slots</strong> 0; <strong>Speed</strong> -10 ft.; <strong>Other Movement</strong> burrow 40 ft</p>\n<p><strong>Excavate (2 PP)</strong> As a standard action, the mech increases its burrow speed to its full movement speed, creating a 25-foot-wide tunnel. Any creature occupying a space it burrows through must succeed at a Reflex save or be pushed to the nearest available space and take medium bludgeoning damage, as a mech weapon with a level equal to the mech’s tier. The Reflex save DC equals 12 + 1/2 × the mech’s tier. On a success, the creature chooses the space they’re moved to and doesn’t take damage. Any creature without a burrow speed automatically fails the save.</p>\n<p><strong>Cost</strong> 2 × tier</p>"
